<h2>File Format Policy</h2>

<div class="important-notice">
    <h3>Critical Policy: Template Toolkit Only</h3>
    <p><strong>All documentation in the Comserv system MUST use Template Toolkit (.tt) format.</strong></p>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No Markdown (.md) files:</strong> Markdown files cannot be rendered by the web-based documentation system</li>
        <li><strong>Web-based system:</strong> The Comserv documentation system is designed for web access, not IDE-only viewing</li>
        <li><strong>Template Toolkit rendering:</strong> All documentation must be processable by the Template Toolkit engine</li>
        <li><strong>Consistent formatting:</strong> HTML markup ensures consistent rendering across all documentation</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p><em>Any .md files found in the system should be converted to .tt format or removed, as they will not be accessible through the documentation system.</em></p>
</div>

<h2>Future Considerations</h2>

<ol>
    <li><strong>Automated Verification:</strong> Implement a script to verify that all files follow this standardization</li>
    <li><strong>Template Updates:</strong> Update template creation tools to automatically include the file path information</li>
    <li><strong>Documentation Generator:</strong> Enhance documentation generators to extract and use the file path information</li>
    <li><strong>Format Enforcement:</strong> Implement checks to prevent creation of non-.tt documentation files</li>
    <li><strong>Migration Tools:</strong> Create tools to convert any remaining non-.tt documentation to proper Template Toolkit format</li>
</ol>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>This standardization improves the maintainability and clarity of the codebase by ensuring that all template and documentation files clearly indicate their location in the repository and follow the Template Toolkit format required by the web-based documentation system.</p>

<p>The policy of using only Template Toolkit (.tt) files ensures that all documentation is accessible through the web interface and maintains consistency with the overall Comserv system architecture.</p>

<p>This makes it easier for developers to navigate the codebase, debug issues, and maintain documentation while ensuring that all documentation is properly integrated with the web-based system.</p>